		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Mt. Doom Release in Richland, WA<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14360'>Joseph "Quickbeam" Conley</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14360&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 28, 2004</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> So finally, after being delayed twice, the Mt. Doom release event was going to be played. Since our card shop had just recently closed, we had it scheduled for 5:30 P.M. at the Round Table Pizza, which is fairly close to where the card store used to be. Anyway, it cost $25 for pizza and all-you-could drink pop. Given the price, my sister Sarah and I were the only two of the Conleys who would make it. <br />
I stuffed my trade binder and a couple deck boxes with tokens and empty sleeves into a backpack, then, as an afterthought, found the pages with our player numbers on them. I seriously doubted we’d get it sanctioned, but there was a *very* slight chance some out-of-towners would show up and I didn’t want to get caught with my pants down. <br />
We headed down there at about 5:15 and arrived at 5:20. Went inside, smiling girl behind the counter. <br />
Girl: “Can I help you?”<br />
Me: “Ah - we’re here for the Lord of the Rings tournament.”<br />
Girl: “What?”<br />
Me: “The Lord of the Rings tournament.”<br />
Girl: “Lord of the Rings tournament?”<br />
Me: “Yeah, the Lord of the Rings tournament.”<br />
Girl: “O-kay…let me talk to the manager.” <br />
Me: “Alright.”<br />
The girl buzzes off to chat with the manager. I’m not worried, since Greg said something about having cleared it up with the manager. <br />
The manager comes out. “Only thing I have is Rubicon - no Lord of the Rings tournament.”<br />
Rubicon? What the -- ?<br />
“Okay, fine, the guy who runs it will be here in a few minutes, I’ll just wait.”<br />
We seat ourselves in the little foyer, wait a little while, at 5:26 Greg arrives holding a cardboard box, orders a couple large pizzas and four fountain drinks. We simply go over and park ourselves at a table. Tech, nothing scheduled, we’ll just play on their tables. Sweet. <br />
We’ve just started on the first glass of pop when a car pulls up outside and Dave Brawn appears, that’s 4, and that is all we’re going to get. So, off we start with the deck-building. <br />
Greg distributes the starters and 4 booster packs a person. I get the Sam starter which cheers me slightly, from what I’d heard online it was the superior. I open my packs and get a lot of minion cards and very few freeps cards. I ended up only have 6 companions in my deck, the 4 Hobbits, Dead Man of Dunharrow, and Aegnor. I also pulled a Cirdan but he must spot 2 Elves to play so that’s no good. I start building my deck and realize to make a 30-card FP’s side I have to include two End of the Games and a Fleet-footed. I decide to start Merry, Pippin, and the Dead Man, and I have two copies of Sam so hopefully I’ll pull him early. I throw together my shadow side with some Far Harad Mercenaries tech and shuffle it a few times, then the pizzas arrive. I dig into the pepperoni, and the four of us eat all but 4 slices of pizza. Finally we get ready to play and since it’ll be Round Robin we just play the guy across the table already, so its…<br />
<br />
G1 vs. Dave Brawn <br />
He has a Frodo starter. We bid, I win 3-0, play Orc Armor and a Hobbit Sword on Merry, move to 2 after removing 2 for the site text. He plays a strength 9 minion that I assign to the Dead Man and drop a End of the Game becoming damage + 1 and killing him. I move on to site 3 and face another Nazgûl Orc, I take a wound and must stop.<br />
He started with two Oathbreakers, he plays Gandalf, a spectral sword, a Dead Man, and moves to site 2 where I play two large Uruks with a sword and give him 4 wounds, he decides to stop at 2. <br />
I heal for the site and play Sam with his Hobbit Sword, as well as Tale of the Great Ring, go to site 4 where he plays 4 minions and a condition. Sam takes a wound, Merry gives one a wound, the Dead Man wins his skirmish, and Pippin is a 5 with the threats added by Merry, he also takes a wound. Two of them are fierce, Merry takes a wound and the Dead Man kills the other. 3 minions out and I’m beat up, no way I’m moving. <br />
Dave plays nothing, but goes to 3 where I drop 1 Uruk which he kills but stops anyway to heal. My fellowship phase, I drop a Hobbit Sword on Frodo and move to 5 where he plays some more nasty guys, but thanks to some Hobbit pumps and Brave and Loyal tech and only take 1 wound on Pippin, but I can’t kill anyone and again must stop. <br />
At site 3 he heals, plays his 6th companion - another Dead Man I believe - and goes to 4 where I drop Far Harad Mercenaries, another Raider who’s + 3 strength and fierce because I have less that 3 minions/pool, and a Uruk. He assigns the Mercenaries to Frodo and the other ones around, kills the Uruk, Gandalf takes a hit, and uses Noble Leaders to boost Frodo to 7, Frodo takes a wound. He stops. <br />
I can play nothing, I move on to site 6 where two minions hit the table, Sam and Dead Man win their skirmishes, I stop to heal.<br />
Dave goes to site 5 where I play 4 Uruks, he just takes 2 wounds though, and manages to kill 2 of them and then doubles into 6 where a lousy draw puts down 4 more minions, it’s 6 on 6 with a strength 7 Uruk on 4 strength Frodo I have no pumps and Frodo takes some burdens, but none of his comps. die. <br />
I heal up, move to 7 where he drops 3 minions, two of which are fierce. I kill the non-fierce one with End of the Game, Sam and Merry each wound the other, and then Dead Man and Sam kill them in the fierce. I move on to site 8 giving him lots of pool, he can only manage 3 minions. Pippin takes a wound, that’s it. <br />
He heals for the site and steps to 7 where I play the Far Harad Mercenaries/Southron guy combo again, and discard a wraith, we’re in the skirmish phase when time is called. I’m one site ahead, Dave gives me the full win. <br />
FW +3, 3 pts. <br />
<br />
Greg beat Sarah, so it’s the winners now - <br />
<br />
G2 vs. Greg Anderson<br />
Greg has the Sam starter and he also got the premier pull of the day: Galadriel. He starts the 4 Hobbits + the Elf-queen, I go with the same fellowship as before. I win the bid 3-0, and play Sam with his sword, Orc Armor, and sword on Frodo, move to 5 where 2 minions come down, Sam takes a wound, the Dead Man wounds the other, I have a boost in my hand so I double into 3 where two more fierce minions hit the table, I end up with Sam and Merry exhausted, Pippin with 2 wounds, Frodo with 1, and the Dead Man still exhausted, but don’t lose anyone. Tech. <br />
He plays a Hobbit sword on Sam and doubles into 3, taking exactly 0 wounds, but I get down Rank and File and have 4 tokens on it by the end. <br />
My turn, I heal Sam twice, Merry twice, Pippin once, discard Sam from hand to heal him again, I have a excellent hand of pumps in my hand so I move to 4 hoping to get a double to site 5. He plays 2 minions, one of which I kill, and step again to site 5 where 3 more come down. Sam takes one, Dead Man, Merry, and Pippin fight, Pippin ends up exhausted but other than that I’m fine. <br />
Greg heals, plays a second Hobbit sword on Frodo, and moves to 4 where I play a two damage + Uruks, Merry takes two wounds and Sam wounds the other once, but there’s still 2 left in the pool and site 5 will add 13 more so he doesn’t risk it and stops. Good thing for him, because I had a sweet Shadow hand set up to drop on him. <br />
I play nothing, and single into 6 where I take a wound on Sam and Merry, stop again to heal. Greg moves to site 5 where several minions comes down, he messes up in the assignment phase and ends up losing Galadriel, but kills one of the other Uruks and doubles into 6, where I play three more minions. He assigns them around, Merry dies, Pippin dies, Sam dies via Rank and File, and Frodo becomes exhausted, so now he has lone Frodo sitting there.  <br />
I heal with the sanctuary and move to site 7 where 3 Orcs come down, Dead Man kills on of them and Sam the other, I double into 8 where 3 more come down, Merry and the Dead Man die, Sam takes a wound, Pippin two wounds, and Frodo one. Crud. <br />
Frodo alone, Greg heals, plays Orc Armor, and moves to 7. I have 3 minions who are free because I spot 2 possessions, I play 5 Uruks, it’s 36 strength on Frodo. He has Tale of the Great Ring, but my guys are massively damage + and I’m a site ahead, and that is time, so he shakes my hand. <br />
FW +3, 6 pts. <br />
<br />
Game 3 vs. Sarah Conley<br />
She has the other Frodo starter, I win the bid 3-0 and double to 3 without any problems, and stop her at 2 thanks to a big damage + 1 Uruk. I manage to stay 1 site ahead of her the rest of the way, winning it by doubling 6-8 with six companions out. (finally drew Aegnor, first time all day), and then singling into 9. She only had 3 minions out, though they were all fierce. The Dead Man and Pippin dies, Sam and Merry killed the others, and that’s game. <br />
FW +3, 9 pts. <br />
<br />
For first place I get a Aragorn, Elessar Telcontar t-shirt, very tech, and a pair of Mt. Doom starters with 4 booster packs. Sarah gets the Sam starter and 4 boosters. Since I helped pay her entry fee, and she generally just gives me all her prizes anyway in exchange for me building her killer decks, I end up with quite a lot of rares, plus some extremely good ones from the starters, including one that had Arwen, QoEaM, Celeborn, and Toldea. I also pulled a second Cirdan, a foil Mordor Fiend (banned!) and afterwards traded Dave for a Galadriel.<br />
<br />
Tourney props:<br />
Greg for running<br />
Round Table for “hosting”<br />
All who showed<br />
The tech Aragorn shirt<br />
Getting the cards I needed to build great decks<br />
Getting an awesome deck idea last night<br />
<br />
Tourney slops:<br />
Those stupid flies that kept buzzing around my head.<br />
The Rubicon (which was a Star Trek convention) people for not keeping a little quieter. Come on, do you need to laugh THAT loud?<br />
Not getting it sanctioned <br />
<br />
Until next time, I am -<br />
<br />
-Quickbeam<br />
